    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "SUBJECT: Mrs. [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "Informant",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "b7c",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "You will recall that a letter was received from the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "above captioned individual dated July 10, 1947, in which she",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "text": "inclosed a newspaper clipping signed \"Radio Ham.\" This news-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "paper clipping contained a coded message which Mrs. [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "decoded. The FBI Laboratory checked Mrs. [REDACTED] decoding of",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "this message and advised that it was substantially correct. The",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "Laboratory's decoding of the message is being set forth below:",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "\"TIRED OF HUMAN NONSENSE WONT AWAIT ATOMIC WAR",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "DISRUPTING ORDER SOLAR SYSTEM SO SENT FLYING",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "text": "DISKS AND WILL SET UP WORLD ORDER UNDER MARTIANS",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "text": "LATE THIS YEAR.\"",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 43,
      "text": "b7c",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 44,
      "text": "tb",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 45,
      "text": "The New York Office was asked to interview Mrs. [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 46,
      "text": "determine from what newspaper the clipping in question was obtained.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 47,
      "text": "They were further instructed to contact this newspaper in an effort",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 48,
      "text": "to ascertain the identity of the person who sent in the coded message,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 49,
      "text": "in order that the person might be interviewed for information concerning",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 50,
      "text": "the alleged receipt of the coded message.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 51,
      "text": "By letter dated September 4, 1947, the New York Office",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 52,
      "text": "advised that they had ascertained from Mrs. [REDACTED] that the coded",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 53,
      "text": "message had appeared in \"Newsday,\" the local newspaper of Nassau and",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 54,
      "text": "Suffolk County, Long Island, New York. The City Editor of this news-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 55,
      "text": "paper stated that the original had been signed only \"Radio Ham\" and",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 56,
      "text": "knew of no way of determining the identity of the writer. It was the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 57,
      "text": "City Editor's opinion that the code had been made up by some local",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 58,
      "text": "\"screwball\" who had been affected by all of the newspaper publicity",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 59,
      "text": "that had been given to stories concerning \"flying discs.\"",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 60,
      "text": "b7c",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 61,
      "text": "The FBI Laboratory has now advised that the FCC maintains",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 62,
      "text": "their amateur records by a geographical breakdown as well as by call",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 63,
      "text": "letters and that the Laboratory could possibly get the names of all",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 64,
      "text": "amateurs in the Bellmore, Long Island, New York Section in the event",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 65,
      "text": "it is desired that another attempt be made to identify the person who",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 66,
      "text": "sent this coded message to the \"Newsday.\"",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 67,
      "text": "62- 93894- 94",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 68,
      "text": "RECOMMENDATION: It is recommended that no further action be taken in",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 69,
      "text": "connection with this matter in view of the opinion expressed by the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 70,
      "text": "City Editor of the \"Newsday\" that the letter received by him signed",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 71,
      "text": "\"Radio Ham\" was from some local \"screwball.\"",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
